{"word":"καθιδρύω","slug":"καθιδρύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καθιδρύω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ύσω</el>) (Causal of <el>καθέζομαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to make to sit down</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to sit down, settle</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>κ. ἐς Ἀργώ</el> <i>to take one's seat</i> in Argos, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to consecrate, dedicate</i>: so in aor1 <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>-ιδρυσάμην</el> and <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>-ίδρῡμαι</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}